# ─── Appendix C — eval_v2 vs eval full-subset comparison ─────────

# Priya's 2025-10-18 repro, extended to all four methods
# Integer-scored fuzzy scorers diverge by ~1 pp on top_1; float-scored
# embedding scorers are equivalent within 0.001.

method           scorer      t1.py    t1.v2    t2.py    t2.v2    t3.py    t3.v2
minilm           float      0.3937   0.3939   0.4543   0.4544   0.4740   0.4740
openai_3small    float      0.4687   0.4687   0.5137   0.5137   0.5297   0.5297
partial_ratio    integer    0.4407   0.4523   0.4913   0.4985   0.4997   0.4997
wratio           integer    0.4223   0.4320   0.4740   0.4802   0.4803   0.4803

# observations:
# - float scorers (embeddings): identical to 3 decimals
# - integer scorers (fuzzy): eval_v2 inflates top_1 by ~1 pp
# - top_3 is invariant regardless of tie-break direction
# recommendation: keep both scripts; use eval.py for canonical runs

